{
    "name": "Inject Nanobots",
    "type": "spell",
    "img": "systems/sfrpg/icons/spells/inject_nanobot.png",
    "data": {
        "description": {
            "chat": "",
            "gmnotes": "",
            "short": "",
            "value": "<p>You concentrate key particles in your blood into tiny biological nanobots that you can inject into a foe with a touch, disrupting and damaging its natural processes. Make a melee attack against the target&rsquo;s EAC; if you hit, the nanobots deal 4d8 damage and swarm through the target&rsquo;s biological or mechanical systems, causing the creature to be @Compendium[sfrpg.conditions.8rIj0ewW4bL8Uph5]{Confused}, as per @Compendium[sfrpg.spells.wSeE9HyAmM7lTdpo]{Confusion}, for 1 round per your caster level. If the target succeeds at a Fortitude save, it takes only half damage and negates the @Compendium[sfrpg.spells.wSeE9HyAmM7lTdpo]{Confusion} effect. A @Compendium[sfrpg.conditions.8rIj0ewW4bL8Uph5]{Confused} target can attempt a Will saving throw at the beginning of its turn each round to end the confusion effect.</p>\n<p>Casting this spell doesn&rsquo;t provoke attacks of opportunity.</p>",
            "unidentified": ""
        },
